EXCEPTION (names, mascot, and royalties)
========================================

Both grants above carry an explicit trademark, naming, and royalty exception:

	LICENSES/exceptions/Oreo-trademarks

The Oreo mascot character, the chest "E-badge", the "Elixpo" and "Oreo" names,
the elixpo.com and *.elixpo.com identifiers, and the brand palette in
brand/MASCOT.md are reserved trademarks of the Elixpo project. The licenses
above grant rights to the code and asset files as files. They do NOT grant
rights to the Elixpo or Oreo brand, nor the right to offer a competing
product or service under the Elixpo or Oreo name. This is what protects the
ecosystem's royalties while keeping the code and assets free and open. See the
exception for the full terms (including permitted referential use).

NOTICE BOARD (per-product reservations)
=======================================

Some Elixpo products ship exclusive artifacts on top of their source - a
published npm package, a VS Code Marketplace extension, a hosted SaaS service,
a paid tier, and so on. Any such product-specific reservation is declared in:

	LICENSES/NOTICE   (the notice board, at the repository root)

Where the NOTICE file adds a reservation for an exclusive artifact, that
reservation governs that artifact, in addition to this LICENSE.

